00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:25,900
Self?

538
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:31,380
You're just a child.
How do you know about self?

539
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,020
If I don't take good care
of your father and you,

540
00:24:34,020 --> 00:24:34,900
I can't imagine

541
00:24:35,660 --> 00:24:37,660
what your father's family
would say about me.

542
00:24:37,800 --> 00:24:38,500
Listen.

543
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,350
When we first got married,
your aunt scolded me

544
00:24:40,350 --> 00:24:41,900
because I couldn't cook.

545
00:24:59,380 --> 00:25:00,850
From the very start, my mom should not

546
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:02,860
move from place to place with my dad.

547
00:25:03,100 --> 00:25:04,860
She used to be the vice manager
at the mall.

548
00:25:04,860 --> 00:25:05,900
That was a good job.

549
00:25:06,140 --> 00:25:07,420
She used to be happier.

550
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:09,900
Now she moves around with my dad.

551
00:25:09,900 --> 00:25:11,580
We've moved to four different cities.

552
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:13,660
My dad moved up.

553
00:25:13,660 --> 00:25:15,260
But my mom can't find

554
00:25:15,260 --> 00:25:16,260
a decent job herself.

555
00:25:17,820 --> 00:25:20,500
She has lost herself because she wants

556
00:25:20,500 --> 00:25:21,980
to please my dad's side of the family.

557
00:25:22,580 --> 00:25:24,140
That's why this is so painful now.

558
00:25:25,820 --> 00:25:28,900
Your mom is making a great sacrifice.

559
00:25:29,180 --> 00:25:31,620
Someone has to sacrifice for the family.

560
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:32,740
Wait.

561
00:25:33,260 --> 00:25:34,220
I get it

562
00:25:34,230 --> 00:25:35,980
